All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ConversorBase
ConversorBase has all the components required to create a new Java Swing interface.
ConversorDistancias
ConversorMonedas adopts the basic attributes from ConversorBase and modifies the final size of the window while, at the same time implementes ActionListener.
ConversorMonedas
ConversorMonedas adopts the basic attributes from ConversorBase and its configurations, at the same time implements ActionListener and ValorCambioMoneda.
ConversorTemperaturas
ConversorTemperaturas adopts the basic attributes from ConversorBase and its configurations, at the same time implementes ActionListener.
Main
Main class with the main method that starts all the program.
MainMenu
MainMenu is the class in charge to display the JOptionPane dialog to start the selection for every type of the conversor (Monedas, Temperatura y Distancias).
ValorCambioMoneda
This interface has two attributes, and both are arrays, the 1st array stores all the values of currency change and the 2nd array stores all the symbols for the corresponding currency's
